author: Christian Datoc
title: Kentucky Woman At McConnell Town Hall Makes Liz Warren Joke
text:
5495654 A Kentucky woman at Mitch McConnell’s Tuesday town hall meeting in Lexington ended a fiery rant, directed at the Senate Majority Leader, by clowning Sen. Elizabeth Warren.
“People don’t have the insurance they need because they’re poor,” she shouted. “They worked those coal miner, and they’re sick. The veterans are sick, and the veterans are broken down.”
WATCH: 
“They’re not getting what they need,” she continued. “And If you can answer any of that I’ll sit down and shut up like Elizabeth Warren.”
It should be noted — per the Washington Examiner — that McConnell did not answer the woman’s questions.
